Service Description

Soar above the clouds and spend a full day exploring the magical world of B=
a Na Hills =97 Da Nang's most spectacular mountain retreat and home to some=
 of the most extraordinary experiences in all of Vietnam.Board the record-b=
reaking cable car and ascend through swirling mist to the summit, where coo=
l mountain air and sweeping panoramic views of Da Nang City set the tone fo=
r an unforgettable day ahead. Cross the iconic Golden Bridge =97 held drama=
tically aloft by two giant stone hands emerging from the clouds =97 before =
wandering through the enchanting Le Jardin D'Amour Flower Gardens and the a=
tmospheric France Wine Cellar. Pause at the serene Linh Ung Pagoda before b=
oarding a second cable car to the charming French Village, where street mus=
icians, art sculptures, the grand Campanile, the Nine Floor Goddess Shrine,=
 and the peaceful Linh Phong Monastery create a scene that feels wonderfull=
y, impossibly far from the Vietnamese coast below. Sip tea at the Tru Vu Te=
a Shop, catch a lively Carnival Performance Show, and take a thrilling free=
 ride on the Slide of Tube Car.Refuel over a generous Vietnamese-Indian buf=
fet lunch =97 with both vegetarian and non-vegetarian Indian dishes on offe=
r =97 before plunging into the excitement of Fantasy Park. Walk through the=
 enchanting Fairy Forest, explore Dinosaur Park, take on the 5D Wild West, =
race through the 4D Death Race, brave the Horror House, and feel your stoma=
ch drop on the exhilarating Free Fall Tower.Note: Vietnamese-Indian buffet =
lunch and cable car rides included. Fantasy Park free rides included as spe=
cified.

Inclusions

Transfers

Indian Lunch

Cable Car Ride (2 Way)

Entrance Tickets

Exclusions

Anything apart from inclusions & personal expenses

Day 3: 26 Aug 2026

 Hoi An Tour with Marble Mountain Visit- Shared Transfers

Service Description

As the afternoon heat softens, set out on an enchanting evening journey fro=
m Da Nang to the magical lantern-lit streets of Hoi An =97 stopping along t=
he way at one of central Vietnam's most spiritually significant and visuall=
y dramatic landmarks.The Marble Mountains =97 five limestone and marble pea=
ks representing the five elements of Asian philosophy: Metal, Wood, Water, =
Fire, and Earth =97 rise dramatically from the coastal plains in a cluster =
of mystical caves, sacred pagodas, and ancient shrines. Explore the atmosph=
eric Tam Thai Pagoda and the revered Linh Ung Pagoda, where Buddhist spirit=
uality permeates every carved stone and incense-scented corridor. At the fo=
ot of the mountains, wander through Non Nuoc Stone Carving Village and admi=
re the extraordinary skill of local artisans whose intricate sculptures hav=
e made this village famous throughout Vietnam.Arrive in Hoi An as the sun s=
ets and the town transforms into a glowing wonderland of coloured lanterns =
and warm evening light. Sit down to a delicious dinner of Hoi An's finest s=
pecialities =97 Cao Lau, Hoanh Thanh wontons, Banh Bao, and the delicate Ba=
nh Vac White Rose dumplings =97 before stepping out into the ancient street=
s for an evening stroll. Cross the iconic Japanese Covered Bridge, a timele=
ss symbol of Hoi An's rich trading heritage, and meander along the Hoai Riv=
er as lanterns shimmer across the water in a scene of pure, effortless beau=
ty.

Inclusions

Shared Transfer

Good English Speaking Guide

