(47, 47, 47);">As the afternoon heat softens, set out on an enchanting even=
ing journey from Da Nang to the magical lantern-lit streets of Hoi An =97 s=
topping along the way at one of central
 Vietnam's most spiritually significant and visually dramatic landmarks.The=
 Marble Mountains =97 five limestone and marble peaks representing the five=
 elements of Asian philosophy: Metal, Wood, Water, Fire, and Earth =97 rise=
 dramatically from the coastal plains
 in a cluster of mystical caves, sacred pagodas, and ancient shrines. Explo=
re the atmospheric Tam Thai Pagoda and the revered Linh Ung Pagoda, where B=
uddhist spirituality permeates every carved stone and incense-scented corri=
dor. At the foot of the mountains,
 wander through Non Nuoc Stone Carving Village and admire the extraordinary=
 skill of local artisans whose intricate sculptures have made this village =
famous throughout Vietnam.Arrive in Hoi An as the sun sets and the town tra=
nsforms into a glowing wonderland
 of coloured lanterns and warm evening light. Sit down to a delicious dinne=
r of Hoi An's finest specialities =97 Cao Lau, Hoanh Thanh wontons, Banh Ba=
o, and the delicate Banh Vac White Rose dumplings =97 before stepping out i=
nto the ancient streets for an evening
 stroll. Cross the iconic Japanese Covered Bridge, a timeless symbol of Hoi=
 An's rich trading heritage, and meander along the Hoai River as lanterns s=
himmer across the water in a scene of pure, effortless beauty.</span></p>
